folder: Stillwell Avenue & Surf Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
(1) Stillwell Ave., north from Coney Island (Reigelmann) Boardwalk to Surf Ave., showing demolition in progress for the extension of this Ave., January 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(2) The same, slightly northward. December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(3) A view north of the Bowery. On the right appears Stratton Walk, which will become a part of this new thoroughfare. December 1923.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

(4) The same as No. 1, at a later date, and showing the new avenue. November 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Stillwell Avenue & Surf Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Stillwell Ave., north from Surf Ave., showing on its N.W. corner the Loew's Theatre building under construction. Also shown is the Coney Island station of the B.M.T. lines.
March 1924.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Stillwell Avenue & Surf Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Stillwell Ave., west side, south of Surf Ave., showing Stillwell's (million dollar) Baths).
June 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.

folder: Stillwell Avenue & Surf Avenue, Brooklyn, NY
text:
Stillwell Ave., north from Surf Ave., showing a view northeast from the B.M.T. terminal station on Stillwell Ave. To the right, partially seen, is a baseball field and stands, and beyond it is the Brooklyn Borough Gas Co. tanks.

October 1928.

Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
